<br>
Now, however, she needed to cool off.<br>
<br>
She'd stopped by her hut to collect a length of linen, then headed down to the pond.  Lysia set her armor, weapons, and the linen in view, then made her way to a low cliff.  It wasn't much taller than she herself was. and combined with the deep water under it made a perfect diving platform.<br>
<br>
Lysia made her dive with only a small splash, and surfaced a few moments later... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 773<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/03 2:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Themiscryan Bathing Pond</span><hr size=1> Hippolyte had been leaning against a post outside the stables, when she had watched Lysia walk down to the pond that was made by the Themodon river floods.  Her lips moved into a slight grin, watching the warrior dive into the water.  <br>
<br>
Out of site for a moment, Hippolyte stepped away from the building and walked over to a small rock that protruded out near the cool waters.  Dressed only in her purple tunic, belt, and short burgandy robe, it was a day of relaxing.  And least so the amazons had hoped.  The sun was out attempting to warm the winter chill from the amazon lands.  Until Demeter blew her cold temper one last time upon them.<br>
<br>
&quot;Water is still a bit cold ..don't you think commander?&quot;  Hippolyte stood there grinning.  Her hands resting on her golden belted hips. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/03 2:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cslrwillow/images/lysia.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Themiscryan Bathing Pond</span><hr size=1> Lysia spluttered a little in surprise.  &quot;My queen!  I didn't expect to see you here.&quot; She swam closer to shore, to where she could stand on the pond bottom.  &quot;It's cold, yeah, but I'm used to it.  Feels good after a morning of sparring.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 775<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/03 2:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Themiscryan Bathing Pond</span><hr size=1> Hipp grinned and bent her knees a bit.  Her hand reaching out to let her fingertips gently touch the water's surface. The small waves lapping her slender digits.  &quot;Well....I suppose you are right.&quot;  Hippolyte suddenly flicked her wrist and her fingers sent water splashing at Lysia.  <br>
<br>
Then suddenly getting up and out of firing range, Hipp laughed.  &quot;There are warmer places to take a bath, commander.&quot; <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/03 3:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Lysia wiped the water off her face, with a dangerous calm.  &quot;That's true, my queen.  But none with such good company.&quot;  She met Hippolyte's eyes, her own icy blue ones flashing.  &quot;Are you sure you don't want to join me?&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 779<br> <font color=#993300>(2/20/03 10:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Hippolyte glanced at the water and then back to the cool gaze of Lysia.  She was in a bit of dilemma.  For one thing...the water was cold..not something Hippolyte cared for.  But, the other was that she didn't want to seem the weak chicken in front of the commander of the warriors.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Endaksi...I suppose I shall,&quot; Hipp's brown eyes glanced about a bit...yes they were in Themiscrya.  But, lately..one never knew who would slip thru the bounderies.  Then she walked over to a tree and began to unlace and unbuckle her leathers.  &quot;I guess cold river water would be good to get cleaned up from riding all day.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Hippolyte smirked and then finally slid almost every bit of clothing from her form.  All that was left was the very thin purple silk tunic.  Walking up the cliff, she stood on the edge.  Her toes wiggling a bit.  Her heart in her throat..knowing full well ..that water was damn cold.<br>
<br>
Shaking it out of her head, Hippolyte dove off the cliff.  Her form speeding down to the dark deep water, and leaving a gentle splash as she sunk down.<br>
<br>
Now deep in the water, Hippolyte was freezing.  But, she forced herself to stay underwater.  Swimming over to where Lysia was.  Reaching out with one hand, she quickly pulled the warrior down under the water and then let go playing.  Hipp shot up to the top of the water, &quot;GOOD HERA...I am sorry..but this is cold!&quot; <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 5:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cslrwillow/images/lysia.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Lysia hadn't expected her queen to take her challenge, so she was still a bit of balance from the dive when Hippolyte dunked her.  <br>
<br>
&quot;I never said it wasn't, my queen. Just that I was used to it.&quot;  The icy eyes flashed again, before she gave Hippolyte a shallow dunking in revenge.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 782<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 5:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> As Lysia pushed her head down, Hippolyte took a deep breath.  Feeling the cold water cover her head.  Swimming back a big, Hippolyte slid out from underneath Lysia's hand.  Rising up from the water, Hippolyte's hands moved up and pushed her wet hair from her face.  And then she smiled to Lysia.  &quot;No...you didn't say it was not cold.  But, I don't know how long I can stay in here.&quot;  Hippolyte's body was turning pail from the chill.  Even her lips began to tremble.  <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

