<br>
Lysia handles the cold in her usual manner - keeping moving even as they talk.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 787<br> <font color=#993300>(2/21/03 9:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Hippolyte nodded, &quot;I think I am going to go see how the fire is doing in my hut.&quot;  Hipp started walking towards the water's edge.  Her slender body trembling in the thin purple fabric that was now clinging to her body as she rose out of the water.  &quot;You can join me if you want.&quot;  Hippolyte glanced over to Lysia, as pulled her boots on and then throwing her burgandy cape around her shivering form. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

