<br>
She put her leathers and weapons back on and dried off with the linen as best she could.  Now she was only mildly uncomfortable, instead of being in danger of freezing solid.  She returned to Hippolyte's side and gave a nod to indicate she was ready to go as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 788<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/03 12:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Hipp smirked at Lysia and then began to walk back to her hut and thru the village.  &quot;The cold water certainly wakes you up.  But, so does falling off a running horse.&quot;  She laughed and then began walking up the steps to her hut.  Hipp smiled.  It felt so good to be back home.  She hoped her father would not call her again...at least..not for a long time.<br>
<br>
The guards of the Vasilissa's hut pulled back the curtains, allowing Hippolyte and Lysia to step thru them.  The hut at least felt warmer, but the chill of the water still was in her bones.   <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

