The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#993300>(2/24/03 11:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cslrwillow/images/lysia.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> She nodded to the guards as they entered, and relaxed at the extra warmth.  Always hot-blooded, it was enough for her.  <br>
<br>
The commander was glad to have her queen back, having only a bare idea of where she'd been.  &quot;Why don't you take the spot near the fire, and I'll go start some tea?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 790<br> <font color=#993300>(2/25/03 9:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> &quot;Efharisto,&quot; Hippolyte thanked Lysia and walked over to the fire that was always kept going in the cold weather.  Picking up a soft fur, she wrapped it around herself and then sat down on another fur.  The heat from the fire felt so good on her chilled body that the wet purple tunic still clung to.  Her wild auburn hair was beginning to dry, it's curls becoming more evident. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#993300>(2/26/03 10:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cslrwillow/images/lysia.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Lysia had been hopeless in the kitchen as a child.  Living on her own had forced her to learn to make at least a few things and tea was one of them.  <br>
<br>
A short search of the cupboards yielded a kettle, tea leaves, and two cups. &quot;Okay, just need some water now,&quot; she muttered to herself.  She found an earthenware jug of it after a few hundred heartbeats and soon after returned to the fire, hanging the kettle over the flame to heat.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 793<br> <font color=#993300>(2/26/03 12:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Hippolyte smiled as Lysia returned.  &quot;So, the warrior makes tea?&quot;  She chidded playfully as she moved over  a bit, offering some of the fur on the floor to Lysia to sit.  Lifting her hands up, Hipp had begun to run her fingers thru her hair to fix the wild strands.   <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#993300>(2/26/03 1:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/cslrwillow/images/lysia.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Lysia grinned.  &quot;It was that, or continue getting teased for not even being able to do that much in the kitchen.  The decision to make was pretty obvious.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Yes, as a warrior, she could have bullied her sisters into stopping the teasing but that just wasn't right. Her animosity was reserved for true enemies.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 795<br> <font color=#993300>(2/27/03 7:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A little fun...</span><hr size=1> Smiling softly, Hippolyte listened to the commander.  &quot;And it wouldn't look good for you to seem dependent on others..in front of the warriors.&quot;  Hipp chuckled, letting the fur fall from her shoulders to the floor.  The fire was finally warming up her body and drying the purple tunic she wore.  <br>
<br>
Her brown eyes glanced to the fire and then back to Lysia.  &quot;I am sorry that I left little word when I left in December.  I hated it.  But, my father came to me in the middle of the night.  He said I had to leave with him right then.&quot;  Her face grew serious and Hippolyte turned her dark eyes back to the flames.  The light flickering in the dark pools.  &quot;I try not to question the wills of the Gods.  But, this time it was not easy.&quot; <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fireofthemiscrya>FireOfThemiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#993300>(2/28/03 1:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A chill...</span><hr size=1> Lysia occupied herself with the tea, soon producing two steaming cups.  She handed one to Hippolyte, and sipped her own.  <br>
<br>
Her expression was closed now, guarded.  &quot;You are my queen... the very granddaughter of our patron Hera.  No more explanation is needed.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hippolyte>Hippolyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 799<br> <font color=#993300>(3/6/03 1:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=436.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/Hippwknife1ezboard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A chill...</span><hr size=1> &quot;Perhaps,&quot; Hippolyte said as she took the cup from Lysia.  &quot;But, when I am gone from Themiscrya.. I feel half a person.   This village is so much apart of me.  As my athelfi are.  You are all my family....it is lonely without you.&quot;  She gave a soft smile and then took a sip of her tea. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
